The paper deals with the problem of finding cycles in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The paper presents a new algorithm for finding even cycles in graphs, which is a problem that falls under the category of graph algorithms. The paper also involves a detailed analysis of capped k-walks, which is a new concept in graph theory. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
